Well, as per Prof. Goodwin's message I guess Cantera doesn't do 2-D 
generalized calculations. However, you can certainly incorporate 
Cantera's chemistry engine into an external code representing your 
system. Depending on what you're trying to represent, you'll need 
various mixing, fluid mechanics, flame velocity, and heat transfer 
models. Such things are often quite system dependant. Perhaps if you 
told us what kind of closed-volume combustion system you're looking 
at we might be able to give you a nudge in the right direction.

Chad
